FBIS4-28803 "dreas114_a_94007" FBIS-EAS-94-114 Daily Report 13 Jun 1994 NORTHEAST ASIA Japan Tokyo's Reaction to DPRK's Withdrawal from IAEA Tokyo's Reaction to DPRK's Withdrawal from IAEA Foreign Ministry Comments OW1406025094 Tokyo NHK General Television Network in Japanese 22005 GMT 13 Jun 94 OW1406025094 Tokyo NHK General Television Network Japanese BFN [Announcer-read report from the NHK 7 O'Clock Morning (2200 GMT) News] [Text] Japanese Foreign Ministry analysts believe that North Korea is taking a tough stand in an attempt to win some kind of compromise to prevent United Nations' sanctions. Japan -- without responding excessively to North Korea's announcement to secede from the IAEA, and by maintaining ties with the United States, the ROK, and China -- wants to strengthen its effort to persuade North Korea to sit down at the discussion table with the international community.
